44722.Meaning: white (especially of hair); white (esp. of hair)
44722.LexemeNotePlain: Also cānus adj. 'white, esp. of hair' < PItal. *kasno- 'grey' < PIE.  *ḱh₁s-no- 'grey'. "Cognate with the word for 'hare' in other IE languages. Lubotsky 1989 connects several other words in initial *ḱ- meaning 'grey': OIr. cíar 'dark-brown' < *ḱh₁-ei-ro-, OIc. hárr, OE. hār 'grey, old' < PGm. *χaira-, RuCS sěrъ, OCz. šěrý, Pl. szary 'grey' < PSl. *xoiro- < *ḱh₁-oi-ro-. Thus, the root ultimately was *ḱh₁-" (MDV)
44722.LexemeNoteHtmlified: Also cānus adj. 'white, esp. of hair' < PItal. *kasno- 'grey' < PIE.  *ḱh₁s-no- 'grey'. "Cognate with the word for 'hare' in other IE languages. Thus, the root ultimately was *ḱh₁-" (MDV)
